    {
      "id": "issue-76-arduino/summer-of-code",
      "type": "issue",
      "ts": "2020-03-11T09:35:56Z",
      "repo": "arduino/summer-of-code",
      "semantic": null,
      "data": {
        "number": 76,
        "title": "Gsoc2020: port FreeRTOS to Portenta",
        "state": "closed",
        "body": "Hello, everyone!\r\nI'm interested in the work of porting the FreeRTOS to Portenta. I have experience in developing operating systems and using rtos. And I have written the compatibility layer of Arduino for AliOS-Things.\r\n\r\nThis is my operating system work, it is not finished yet: [SimpleKernel](https://github.com/MRNIU/SimpleKernel)\r\nAnd this is the Arduino compatible layer I wrote for AliOS-Things: [AliOS-Things_ArduinoFramework](https://github.com/MRNIU/AliOS-Things)\r\n\r\nThis is a challenging job for me, and I will write my work plan in as much detail as possible in the proposal.\r\n\r\nThere is a problem. The [Application Instructions](https://github.com/arduino/summer-of-code/blob/master/how-to-apply.md#during-the-application-phase-february-20th---march-31st) requires a bug to be solved. Is there a requirement for the difficulty of this bug?\r\n\r\nThink you!"
      }
    },
